 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "PortalCurator-LLM ⊣ PortalGovernor (portal.policy, eight checks: rbac ·
  source-provenance-gate · license-scope-gate (17 U.S.C. §107 fair-use-
  excerpt ceiling, this actor's domain-unique HARD check) ·
  disclosure-gate (16 CFR Part 255 native-advertising disclosure, second
  domain-unique HARD check) · licensed-disclosure · confidence-floor ·
  sensitive-subject-gate · correction-requests-always-escalate), langgraph
  StateGraph (portal.operation), append-only audit ledger
  (portal.store/ledger + append-ledger!). A phase 0→3 staged-autonomy gate
  (portal.phase) sits on top of the governor and can only narrow, never
  widen, what the governor already allowed. 35 tests / 141 assertions
  green (`clojure -M:dev:test`), demo runnable end-to-end
  (`clojure -M:dev:run`). Optional `portal.marketdata-bridge` integration
  with the sibling cloud-itonami-isic-6311 market-data actor is covered by
  a separate opt-in test suite (`clojure -M:dev:test:market-data`) that
  isn't required for `portal.*` core to stay green."}
